\end{align*}

Correct! 

\(y = x^2 + 3\) is not a solution since

\begin{align*}
\frac{dy}{dx} - 3   =\amp\   2x                               \\
\frac{d}{dx}\left[x^2 + 3\right] - 3    =\amp\   2x                               \\
2x - 3  =\amp\   2x \quad \leftarrow \text{false} 
\end{align*}

